narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: You read three genres, and international texts in each: lyric, epic, drama, in that order. One paper per genre makes the workload very manageable. You read some grrrreat texts (esp. in lyric); Lectures are what you make out of them. TAKE THE TRUMPENER SECTION.
Take it if you need it for Lit, or if you're interested in problems of translation, performativity, etc. If you're just in it for a WR credit, you might get frustrated.
I would recommend Katie Trumpener in teaching anything, but not necessarily this class because it was a bit boring and uninspiring.
